Package se.arkalix.net.http.client

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HttpClientConnection
    Connection useful for sending HTTP requests to a single remote socket address.
    HttpClientResponse
    An incoming HTTP response.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    HttpClient
    Allows for the creation of TCP connections through which HTTP messages can be sent.
    HttpClient.Builder
    Builder useful for creating HttpClient instances.
    HttpClientRequest
    An outgoing HTTP request.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    HttpClientConnectionException
    Signifies that some HTTP client failed to establish some HttpClientConnection.
    HttpClientException
    Signifies that some HTTP client action related to a HttpClientConnection failed.
    HttpClientResponseException
    Signifies that some HTTP response received via a HttpClientConnection either describes or contains an error and, therefore, will not be processed.
    HttpClientResponseRejectedException
    Signifies that some HTTP response received via a HttpClientConnection was rejected due to not satisfying some arbitrary requirement.
